Rhodium-plated, straight-line lever escapement, monometallic balance, shock absorber, self compensating flat balance spring. Bezel: Fixed bezel with tachimeter function Crystal: Hesalite crystal Dial: Matte black dial with painted luminous baton indexes, sunk guilloche subsidiary dials for the constant seconds with , the 12-hour and 30-minute registers, outer minute/seconds and 1/5th seconds divisions. Luminous white baton hands. Bracelet: Brushed and polished stainless steel bracelet with push button fold over clasp. Fits 8" wrist. Condition: Pre Owned Engravings: See Below Original Box and Documentation This watch is the Gemini VI Mission watch with the flight patch printed on the dial at nine o’clock. The blue patch for the mission (the seconds recorder dial) was designed by Command Pilot Walter M Schirra. The hexagonal shape and the trajectory through the stars both relate to the mission being the sixth in the Gemini program, and the Gemini VI spacecraft is shown between the twin stars Castor and Pollux as per the location of the rendezvous point.
